{"key":"processedPost-11037523","value":{"id":11037523,"first":11034421,"last":11058199,"when":1252644299,"utime":"09/11/09 07:44 AM","content":"The tub with holes was only for colonization.&nbsp; For indoor fruiting, you can use open air and just lay a sheet of plastic loosely over the basket.&nbsp; Lift it up several times per day when you mist.&nbsp; Some growers fruit laundry baskets in open air at normal room humidity, but performance is not as good.&nbsp; If you do it in open air, you'll notice the straw around the edges dries out, which is actually good.&nbsp; The straw inside is still moist, and the dry straw forms somewhat of a 'contamination barrier' protecting what's inside.<br />RR","title":"Re: Laundry Basket Humidity - QUESTIONS","forum":"Mushroom Cultivation"}}